Content:
yes ... I wanted to make longer block times to stop people making crazy amounts of tx every minute... but verushash doesn t work with ac_blocktime... 
The snapshot height is actually an unknown variable until it happens, well within about 10 blocks... but notarizations dont always happen every 10 blocks either so it could be 20 or even 30 blocks before the 1440 multiple each day.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: ok now we can get the range paid before doing the release. Once the snapshot happens, you can call payments info to see what range was chosen. Then getsnapshot to find your address ranks. You cant move the coins to get them into the range, but you can issue a release to your advantage. ie, if you have many address i the range release as much as possible, if you have very few try to release the smallest amount (5M) before someone else releases it all.

Author: gcharang#6833
Content:
> before someone else releases it all.

Not nitpicking, but isn't this kinda un enforceable? who ever mines the block can control which transaction will get through(if there are any competing release transactions)

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: sure, but then that person has to mine a longer chain also, or it will be rorged  üòâ

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: something like, make release you want, then hitting the chain with 100 CPUS at once to make sure your release is the one included in the chain would be a stragegy one could use üòÜ

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: This si why I used verushash, as it has a very fast difficulty adjustment window

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: using equihash we would ilikely end up with a stalled chain after a few days
